	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello.&nbsp;&nbsp;Niltsaria Fastfeets here 51 Wanderer on Sol Ro.  At 18 there are many places you can go that are just right for you..  You have already read HHK, HHP, NK, PC, LoIO, There are tons of places you can go for exp and loot etc..  When I was lvl 18 Yes I had a 38 SK funding my push, so it made it easier.  (those were the days long before KEI) At 14 I left Oasis of Marr almost to never look back.  I got in several groups in Upper Guk, and soloed some stuff around Runnyeye and Lavastorm until 16. Then it was off to see the moon.  I discovered PC and I lived there until 24 (took me a while, but I did... about this time KEI came out and I started utilizing all my resources.  I became a crack (KEI) addict.) Anyway I left PC at 24 and decided I was going to see the world.  I found a home in Upper Guk at the ancient Croc spawn.  There I began to work on Fishing, Swimming, and maxing out spell casting since the 16 minute spawn timer. I left there around 32 and went to Twilight Sea.  There I killed elementals until 34 and then I lived in Dawnshroud Peaks for quite a while quad kiting Zelniaks, Large Zelniaks. I left the wolves alone due to socialness and besides that.. they are wolves.  I lived in Dawnshroud until about lvl 38 until the Zelniaks started to go Light Blue. Then I moved on to the single rockhopper (if they were up) or headed to Velious where I began quad kiting Ulthorks in EW near the giant camp.  Not near Kael.  Then around 44 the ulthorks started greening out and I moved onto the Ry`gorr fort in EW until 46 then I spent some time in CC to get 49. New spells and a whole new world opened up.. Well, that is what I did... Others may not agree with it but it is what worked for me.  Good luck on your endeavour.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
